_2` (room mic) via JACK. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCS-015 | — | - daemon opens two JACK ports `cypherclaw-capture:in_contact` and `cypherclaw-capture:in_room`<br/>- each maintains a 60-second numpy ring buffer at 48 kHz<br/>- exposes `get_window(source, duration_sec, offset_sec) -> np.ndarray` for the moment-detector to pull recent windows<br/>- handles JACK xruns gracefully (logs, does not crash)<br/>- tests with a synthetic JACK input fixture verify ring-buffer correctness, window extraction, and xrun recovery |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 7 | T-007 | Implement interesting-moment detector: novelty (spectral flux) + transient density + RMS thresholds + duration-min/max gating. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCS-016 | — | - `sample_capture_daemon.py::InterestingMomentDetector` pulls 1-second windows every 250 ms<br/>- flags a window when: `spectral_flux > 0.6 * recent_median` AND `rms > -45 dBFS` AND `transient_count >= 2` AND `since_last_capture > 30 sec`<br/>- on flag, expands to a 4–8 second window centered on the flagged sub-window (length proportional to spectral richness)<br/>- thresholds are tunable via env / config<br/>- tests with canned audio fixtures (silence, footsteps, dishwasher hum, music) verify expected flag/no-flag for each |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 8 | T-008 | Auto-tag captured samples: arc phase, mood, presence, time-of-day, plus heuristic acoustic tags (warm if low spectral centroid, metallic if high+narrow band, transient if high transient density, etc.). | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCS-017 | — | - `sample_capture_daemon.py::auto_tag(window, context) -> dict` returns a dict mergeable into `SampleRecord`<br/>- arc_phase / mood / presence pulled from `/tmp/organism_state.json` and `/tmp/room_presence.json`<br/>- character tags derived from heuristics: spectral_centroid<800Hz → \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"warm\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"; narrow-band high-centroid → \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\