CHANGELOG.md:53:- Added the CypherClaw narrative API regression suite plus a minimal auth gate (T-005@20260502T001347Z): `cypherclaw.narrative_api.create_app(...)` now accepts an optional `auth_token` keyword that, when set, requires every endpoint to carry a matching `X-Narrative-Auth` header (missing/wrong → 401); empty/unset preserves the existing auth-disabled behavior so T-010's env-var pull and startup warning land cleanly. `tests/test_narrative_api_memory.py` and `tests/test_narrative_api_events.py` now pin the four scenario floors (success path, auth failure when enabled, bad input validation, downstream-engine error handling) for `POST /memory/search`, `GET /events`, and `POST /events`, plus 503 fallback behavior when the deploy-side `cypherclaw.narrative.{memory,events}` package is absent and append-returns-None record synthesis. `pytest --cov=cypherclaw.narrative_api` reports 84% module coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:91:- Added repo-backed sample-capture service wiring for the sampler rollout: `my-claw/systemd/cypherclaw-sample-capture.service` now runs `sample_capture_daemon.py` as `User=user` from the project virtualenv with `Restart=always`, `LimitMEMLOCK=infinity`, and `After`/`Requires` on `cypherclaw-jack.service`; `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now best-effort starts that service after the AV stack comes up; and `tests/test_cypherclaw_boot_runtime.py` pins both the unit-file contract and the boot-script hook.
CHANGELOG.md:93:- Added `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md` to fill the gap between the sampler PRD and the musicianship roadmap: it lists the landed sampler components (`sample_capture_daemon.py`, `sample_capture_verify.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, `sampler_dispatch.py`, `synthesis/sampler_effects.scd`, `render/antipatterns.py`), traces the end-to-end signal flow from JACK input through capture, tagging, `index.sqlite`, dispatch, the `sw_sampler_fx` bus, and the master bus, names both live anti-pattern detectors (`sampler_dominating`, `sampler_silent_quintet_member`), enumerates integration seams (identity, cast planner, mix engine, composer, operator diagnostics), and explicitly flags `SampleLibrary`, `SampleSelector`, `sw_sampler.scd`, and quintet identity convergence as still pending; `tests/test_cypherclaw_sampler_architecture.py` pins the doc's required sections, the referenced file paths, and the live anti-pattern names so future renames or section drops force the doc to update with the code.
CHANGELOG.md:94:- Updated `docs/cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md` to describe the active quintet direction: `sw_bell_warm`, `sw_bowed`, `sw_breath`, `sw_pad`, and the new `sw_sampler` memory voice; the roadmap now separates landed sampler modules (`sample_capture_daemon.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, `sampler_dispatch.py`, `sampler_effects.scd`, anti-pattern checks) from still-pending identity/library/SynthDef convergence so the documentation matches the tree's real partial-rollout state.
CHANGELOG.md:104:- Added course-driven self-critique and revision targets: `self_critique.py` now maps production-course chapter concepts (mode_scale, harmonic_function, meter_groove, counterpoint_relation, synthesis_architecture, mix_role, spatial_intent, genre_strategy, transition_type, phase_profile) to concrete ear-engine metric thresholds via `COURSE_METRIC_MAP`; `thresholds_for_course()` merges per-section course metadata into quality thresholds (stricter wins); `critique_score_with_course()` returns a `CourseCritiqueReport` with `CourseFailure` attribution naming the specific course concept behind each metric violation; `revision_targets_from_failures()` maps failures to `RevisionTargets` specifying which musical dimensions (form, harmony, rhythm, register, mix, strategy) are open for bounded revision without changing piece identity; `revise_score()` accepts an optional `course` kwarg; `tracker_compiler.py` and `duet_composer.py` fallback paths now pass section production_course to `revise_score`.
CHANGELOG.md:109:- Added artistic identity portfolio reporting and surface snapshots: new `portfolio_report.py` module provides `derive_portfolio_report()` for comprehensive identity summaries from repertoire metrics, preferred forms/modes, motif counts, practice block coverage with EMSD course codes, growth-state keys, and ear quality averages; and `derive_surface_snapshot()` for face/operator display data (current song title, section caption, practice block, artistic-intent line). Graceful degradation handles empty repertoire, missing fields, corrupt score trees, and absent growth state without hallucinating data.
CHANGELOG.md:112:- Added pre-performance self-critique and bounded revision passes: new `self_critique.py` module provides `preview_score()` for offline metric analysis, `critique_score()` for threshold-based quality gating, and `revise_score()` for one bounded rewrite attempt that preserves piece identity (key, mood, tempo) while improving at least one failed metric.
CHANGELOG.md:130:- Added a concrete score-tree composition spec for the next songwriting pass: `cypherclaw-score-tree-composition-spec.md` now defines the piece commission layer, narrative brief contract, section-function grammar, score-tree data model, recursive composer, composition gate, tracker compiler, repertoire score-tree memory, and rollout phases needed to move CypherClaw from short tracker-first sketches toward longer, more varied composed pieces.
CHANGELOG.md:143:- Collapsed split boot ownership for the core AV stack: `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now delegates audio/composer/face/gallery/room-listener/sample startup to `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh`, which keeps one authority for those daemons instead of racing duplicate boot paths.
CHANGELOG.md:148:- Relaxed composer restart verification to the real steady-state condition: `restart_composer.sh` now waits for any healthy `duet_composer.py` process instead of only trusting the very first child PID, which avoids false failures during the current live startup race.
CHANGELOG.md:151:- Tightened the cold-boot wrapper to avoid daemon duplication: it now waits for `SuperCollider:out_1` before launching the meter, and it only backfills `room_listener.py`, `sample_playback_engine.py`, and `face_display.py` if another startup source has not already brought them up during the same boot.
CHANGELOG.md:152:- Made the cold-boot wrapper opportunistic instead of combative: if `scsynth` and `duet_composer.py` are already present from another startup path, `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now skips `start_audio.sh` / `restart_composer.sh` entirely and only backfills the missing meter/listener surface.
CHANGELOG.md:174:- Expanded CypherClaw boot coverage for the EMSD sampler path: `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now starts `theramini_listener.py` and `contact_listener.py` alongside the room listener so the stable sample aliases can refresh during unattended startup instead of remaining planned-but-missing files.
CHANGELOG.md:176:- Wired the next EMSD runtime pass into live state: added `emsd_runtime.py`, taught `duet_composer.py` to build a typed EMSD context per tracker song and publish arc/mix/sample/DSP/identity fields into `/tmp/composer_state.json`, extended `repertoire_memory.py` to retain `patch_name`, and taught `self_listener.py` to publish `/tmp/glyph_audio_features.json` by combining live audio analysis with composer/cadence state for GlyphWeave-facing consumers.
CHANGELOG.md:177:- Built the first end-to-end EMSD package: added a 40-course curriculum catalog plus generated `my-claw/curriculum/EMSD-*` scaffolds, and implemented `sound_palette_lab.py`, `sample_lab.py`, `mix_engine.py`, `procedural_arc.py`, `dsp_scene_lab.py`, `artistic_identity.py`, and `capstone_engine.py` so the electronic music production roadmap now exists as runnable code and tests instead of only a brief.
CHANGELOG.md:212:- Added SenseWeave operator diagnostics to daemon `/status`, including score tree, section function, arrangement curve, ear metrics, sample source, master bus, self-listener, and independent rollout flags for curriculum/exercise, preview render, self-critique, and long-form suites.
CHANGELOG.md:215:- Expanded the CypherClaw presence/cadence spec into an implementation blueprint with research-backed daily and weekly cadence rules, silence architecture, social-synchrony guardrails, CPU-safe rollout phases, and a concrete cadence-state runtime contract.
CHANGELOG.md:229:- Taught Telegram `/prd` to load stage order from `sdp/execution-roadmap.md` and batch mappings from `sdp/execution-roadmap.queue-map.json`, so roadmap output follows the current clone/identity/embodiment/publication plan instead of a stale hardcoded stage list.
CHANGELOG.md:277:- Added an interactive startup wizard that asks onboarding questions one at a time.
CHANGELOG.md:278:- Added heuristic follow-up questions when startup answers are vague or underspecified.
CHANGELOG.md:280:- Added startup artifacts: `docs/STARTUP_PROFILE.md`, `docs/STARTUP_TRANSCRIPT.md`, and `.promptclaw/onboarding/startup-session.md`.
CHANGELOG.md:281:- Added agent roster customization and capability inference during startup.
